Note:
SCHEMA - Generic Schema AST (Tier 1)

A neutral, format-agnostic AST that can losslessly represent:
  - JSON Schema (Draft 2020-12)
  - Apache Avro schemas
  - Protocol Buffers descriptors
  - OpenAPI 3.1 component schemas
  - Runa-native schemas (runa_schema.runa)

A SchemaNode is a tagged value whose data slot interpretation depends on
its kind. The tree is owned by the caller; schema_destroy walks the tree
and frees every owned allocation.

NODE KINDS:
  SCHEMA_OBJECT     payload = List<ObjectField>
  SCHEMA_ARRAY      payload = SchemaNode (item type)
  SCHEMA_STRING     payload = StringConstraints record
  SCHEMA_INTEGER    payload = IntegerConstraints record
  SCHEMA_FLOAT      payload = FloatConstraints record
  SCHEMA_BOOLEAN    payload = 0 (no parameters)
  SCHEMA_NULL       payload = 0 (no parameters)
  SCHEMA_UNION      payload = List<SchemaNode> (variants)
  SCHEMA_REFERENCE  payload = String (named reference)
  SCHEMA_ENUM       payload = List<String> (allowed values)
  SCHEMA_ANY        payload = 0 (always accepts)

Layout (SchemaNode, 32 bytes):
  offset  0 : kind          (8 bytes, see SCHEMA_* constants)
  offset  8 : payload       (8 bytes, type-dependent)
  offset 16 : title         (8 bytes, String pointer or 0 - human title)
  offset 24 : description   (8 bytes, String pointer or 0 - long-form docs)

Layout (ObjectField, 40 bytes):
  offset  0 : name          (8 bytes, String pointer)
  offset  8 : schema        (8 bytes, SchemaNode pointer)
  offset 16 : required      (8 bytes, 0 or 1)
  offset 24 : default       (8 bytes, ConfigValue pointer or 0)
  offset 32 : description   (8 bytes, String pointer or 0)

Layout (StringConstraints, 32 bytes):
  offset  0 : min_length    (8 bytes, -1 if unbounded)
  offset  8 : max_length    (8 bytes, -1 if unbounded)
  offset 16 : pattern       (8 bytes, String pointer or 0 - regex source)
  offset 24 : format        (8 bytes, see FORMAT_* constants)

Layout (IntegerConstraints, 40 bytes):
  offset  0 : has_min       (8 bytes)
  offset  8 : min_value     (8 bytes)
  offset 16 : has_max       (8 bytes)
  offset 24 : max_value     (8 bytes)
  offset 32 : multiple_of   (8 bytes, 0 if unset)

Layout (FloatConstraints, 40 bytes):
  offset  0 : has_min       (8 bytes)
  offset  8 : min_value     (8 bytes, Float pointer)
  offset 16 : has_max       (8 bytes)
  offset 24 : max_value     (8 bytes, Float pointer)
  offset 32 : exclusive     (8 bytes, 0=inclusive, 1=both exclusive)

A ValidationIssue (24 bytes) is the diagnostic value returned by
schema_validate. It records a JSON-pointer-style path identifying the
offending sub-value and a human-readable message:
  offset  0 : path           (8 bytes, String pointer)
  offset  8 : message        (8 bytes, String pointer)
  offset 16 : code           (8 bytes, ERROR_* constant)

References:
  - JSON Schema Draft 2020-12  https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema
  - Apache Avro 1.11           https://avro.apache.org/docs/1.11.1/specification/
  - Protocol Buffers           https://protobuf.dev/programming-guides/proto3/
  - OpenAPI 3.1                https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.1.0
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dict
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/string_builder.runa" as SB
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/config/config.runa" as Cfg
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/intrinsics/builtins.runa" as Builtins
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/text/regex.runa" as Regex
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/identity/uuid.runa" as UUID
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/net/ipv4_address.runa" as IPv4
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/net/ipv6_address.runa" as IPv6
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/net/url.runa" as URL
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/time/date.runa" as Date
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/time/time_of_day.runa" as TOD

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Note: SchemaNode is 64 bytes. The first 32 bytes are the original layout
Note: (kind, payload, title, description). The trailing 32 bytes carry
Note: extension slots populated for kind-specific advanced keywords:
Note:   offset 32: extras pointer (object/integer/float/array extras record, or 0)
Note:   offset 40: definitions dict (root schemas store the $defs registry, or 0)
Note:   offset 48: reserved (0)
Note:   offset 56: reserved (0)
Let SCHEMA_NODE_SIZE be 64
Let OBJECT_FIELD_SIZE be 40
Let STRING_CONSTRAINTS_SIZE be 32
Let INTEGER_CONSTRAINTS_SIZE be 40
Let FLOAT_CONSTRAINTS_SIZE be 40
Let VALIDATION_ISSUE_SIZE be 24
Note: Array payload record layout (32 bytes):
Note:   offset  0: item_schema pointer
Note:   offset  8: min_items (sentinel 0 minus 1 = unbounded)
Note:   offset 16: max_items (sentinel 0 minus 1 = unbounded)
Note:   offset 24: unique_items flag (0 or 1)
Let ARRAY_PAYLOAD_SIZE be 32

Note: Object extras record layout (32 bytes):
Note:   offset  0: additional_properties_schema (SchemaNode pointer, or 0)
Note:   offset  8: additional_properties_policy (0=not set, 1=false-reject-all,
Note:              2=true-allow-all, 3=schema-constrained)
Note:   offset 16: dependent_required (Dictionary<String, List<String>>, or 0)
Note:   offset 24: min_properties (sentinel 0 minus 1 = unbounded)
Let OBJECT_EXTRAS_SIZE be 32

Note: Integer/Float extras record layout (32 bytes):
Note:   offset  0: exclusive_min int64 value
Note:   offset  8: exclusive_min_set (0 or 1)
Note:   offset 16: exclusive_max int64 value
Note:   offset 24: exclusive_max_set (0 or 1)
Let NUMERIC_EXTRAS_SIZE be 32

Note: Array extras record layout (16 bytes):
Note:   offset  0: prefix_items (List<SchemaNode> for positional schemas, or 0)
Note:   offset  8: contains_schema (SchemaNode pointer for "must contain", or 0)
Let ARRAY_EXTRAS_SIZE be 16

Note: AP policy constants for the additional_properties slot.
Let AP_POLICY_UNSET be 0
Let AP_POLICY_FALSE be 1
Let AP_POLICY_TRUE be 2
Let AP_POLICY_SCHEMA be 3

Let SCHEMA_OBJECT be 1
Let SCHEMA_ARRAY be 2
Let SCHEMA_STRING be 3
Let SCHEMA_INTEGER be 4
Let SCHEMA_FLOAT be 5
Let SCHEMA_BOOLEAN be 6
Let SCHEMA_NULL be 7
Let SCHEMA_UNION be 8
Let SCHEMA_REFERENCE be 9
Let SCHEMA_ENUM be 10
Let SCHEMA_ANY be 11
Let SCHEMA_AND be 12
Let SCHEMA_NOT be 13
Let SCHEMA_ALL_OF be 14
Let SCHEMA_ONE_OF be 15
Let SCHEMA_CONST be 16

Note: String format vocabulary aligned with JSON Schema Draft 2020-12.
Let FORMAT_NONE be 0
Let FORMAT_EMAIL be 1
Let FORMAT_URL be 2
Let FORMAT_UUID be 3
Let FORMAT_DATE be 4
Let FORMAT_TIME be 5
Let FORMAT_DATE_TIME be 6
Let FORMAT_DURATION be 7
Let FORMAT_IPV4 be 8
Let FORMAT_IPV6 be 9
Let FORMAT_HOSTNAME be 10
Let FORMAT_REGEX be 11
Let FORMAT_JSON_POINTER be 12
Let FORMAT_URI be 13
Let FORMAT_URI_REFERENCE be 14
Let FORMAT_IDN_EMAIL be 15
Let FORMAT_IDN_HOSTNAME be 16
Let FORMAT_IRI be 17
Let FORMAT_URI_TEMPLATE be 18
Let FORMAT_RELATIVE_JSON_POINTER be 19

Note: Composition operators for schema_compose.
Let COMPOSE_AND be 1
Let COMPOSE_OR be 2
Let COMPOSE_NOT be 3

Note: Validation error codes.
Let ERROR_TYPE_MISMATCH be 1
Let ERROR_MIN_LENGTH be 2
Let ERROR_MAX_LENGTH be 3
Let ERROR_PATTERN be 4
Let ERROR_FORMAT be 5
Let ERROR_MIN_VALUE be 6
Let ERROR_MAX_VALUE be 7
Let ERROR_MULTIPLE_OF be 8
Let ERROR_MISSING_FIELD be 9
Let ERROR_ENUM_VIOLATION be 10
Let ERROR_REFERENCE_UNRESOLVED be 11
Let ERROR_UNION_NO_MATCH be 12

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTRAINT CONSTRUCTORS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate a StringConstraints with the supplied bounds and format. -1 in
either bound means unbounded; FORMAT_NONE means no semantic-format check.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 32 bytes and store the four fields. Pattern is duplicated to
guarantee owned lifetime.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(p) where p is pattern length (for the duplicate). Space: O(p).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "string_constraints_create" takes min_length as Integer, max_length as Integer, pattern as Integer, format as Integer returns Integer:
    Let c be proc allocate from Layout with STRING_CONSTRAINTS_SIZE
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 0, min_length
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 8, max_length
    Let dup be 0
    If pattern is not equal to 0:
        Set dup to proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with pattern
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 16, dup
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 24, format
    Return c
End Process

@Reasoning
Free a StringConstraints record. Releases the pattern string if owned.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free the pattern (if non-zero), then free the record.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Safe to call with a null pointer (no-op).
@End Security_Scope
Process called "string_constraints_destroy" takes c as Integer returns Integer:
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let p be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, 16
    If p is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with p
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with c
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Allocate an IntegerConstraints with optional min/max and multiple_of.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 40 bytes; store the five fields in order.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "integer_constraints_create" takes has_min as Integer, min_value as Integer, has_max as Integer, max_value as Integer, multiple_of as Integer returns Integer:
    Let c be proc allocate from Layout with INTEGER_CONSTRAINTS_SIZE
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 0, has_min
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 8, min_value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 16, has_max
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 24, max_value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 32, multiple_of
    Return c
End Process

@Reasoning
Free an IntegerConstraints record.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free the record (no owned children).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Safe to call with a null pointer (no-op).
@End Security_Scope
Process called "integer_constraints_destroy" takes c as Integer returns Integer:
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with c
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Allocate a FloatConstraints with optional bounds.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 40 bytes; store fields.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "float_constraints_create" takes has_min as Integer, min_value as Integer, has_max as Integer, max_value as Integer, exclusive as Integer returns Integer:
    Let c be proc allocate from Layout with FLOAT_CONSTRAINTS_SIZE
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 0, has_min
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 8, min_value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 16, has_max
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 24, max_value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 32, exclusive
    Return c
End Process

@Reasoning
Free a FloatConstraints record. Pointer fields are owned by the caller's
Float allocator so we do not free them here.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free the record only.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Safe to call with a null pointer (no-op).
@End Security_Scope
Process called "float_constraints_destroy" takes c as Integer returns Integer:
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with c
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: OBJECT FIELD CONSTRUCTORS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate an ObjectField with the supplied name, child schema and required
flag. The default and description fields default to 0 and can be set later
with object_field_set_default / object_field_set_description.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Duplicate the name, allocate the 40-byte record, store fields, leave
default/description null.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) for name copy. Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure or null name.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "object_field_create" takes name as Integer, schema as Integer, required_flag as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If schema is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nm be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with name
    If nm is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let f be proc allocate from Layout with OBJECT_FIELD_SIZE
    If f is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with nm
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 0, nm
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 8, schema
    Let req be 0
    If required_flag is not equal to 0:
        Set req to 1
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 16, req
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 24, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 32, 0
    Return f
End Process

@Reasoning
Attach a default value (ConfigValue) to a field. The field assumes
ownership; an existing default is destroyed.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free the prior default if any, then store the new pointer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(d) where d is prior default subtree size. Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null field input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "object_field_set_default" takes f as Integer, default_value as Integer returns Integer:
    If f is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let prior be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 24
    If prior is not equal to 0:
        proc config_value_destroy from Cfg with prior
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 24, default_value
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Attach a description string to a field. Duplicated so the field owns it.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free any prior description and duplicate the new one.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null field input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "object_field_set_description" takes f as Integer, description as Integer returns Integer:
    If f is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let prior be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 32
    If prior is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with prior
    End If
    Let dup be 0
    If description is not equal to 0:
        Set dup to proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with description
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 32, dup
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Read the field name pointer (not owned by caller).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "object_field_name" takes f as Integer returns Integer:
    If f is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Read the field's child schema pointer.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 8.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "object_field_schema" takes f as Integer returns Integer:
    If f is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 8
End Process

@Reasoning
Read the field's required flag.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 16.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 (not required) on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "object_field_is_required" takes f as Integer returns Integer:
    If f is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 16
End Process

@Reasoning
Read the field's default ConfigValue pointer.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 24.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input or no default.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "object_field_default" takes f as Integer returns Integer:
    If f is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 24
End Process

@Reasoning
Free an ObjectField. Deallocates the name, the description, the default,
and recursively the child schema.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free each owned pointer if present, then the record itself.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(s) where s is child schema size. Space: O(d) recursion depth.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Safe to call with null (no-op).
@End Security_Scope
Process called "object_field_destroy" takes f as Integer returns Integer:
    If f is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nm be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 0
    If nm is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with nm
    End If
    Let sch be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 8
    If sch is not equal to 0:
        proc schema_destroy with sch
    End If
    Let def be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 24
    If def is not equal to 0:
        proc config_value_destroy from Cfg with def
    End If
    Let desc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 32
    If desc is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with desc
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with f
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SCHEMA NODE CONSTRUCTORS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate a SchemaNode with the given kind and payload. Title and
description default to 0; use schema_set_title / schema_set_description.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 32 bytes and zero the metadata slots.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_create" takes kind as Integer, payload as Integer returns Integer:
    Let n be proc allocate from Layout with SCHEMA_NODE_SIZE
    If n is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with n, 0, kind
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with n, 8, payload
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with n, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with n, 24, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with n, 32, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with n, 40, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with n, 48, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with n, 56, 0
    Return n
End Process

@Reasoning
Convenience: build a SCHEMA_OBJECT with an empty field list.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Create the empty list, then construct the node.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_create_object" returns Integer:
    Let lst be proc list_create from List
    If lst is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let n be proc schema_create with SCHEMA_OBJECT, lst
    If n is equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with lst
        Return 0
    End If
    Return n
End Process

@Reasoning
Build a SCHEMA_ARRAY whose item type is the supplied schema, with full
JSON Schema array cardinality constraints (minItems, maxItems,
uniqueItems). Pass -1 for min_items or max_items to indicate the
respective bound is unset. Pass 0 for unique_items to skip uniqueness
enforcement, 1 to require all array elements be distinct.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate a 32-byte ArrayPayload record:
  offset  0: item_schema pointer
  offset  8: min_items
  offset 16: max_items
  offset 24: unique_items flag
Then wrap the payload in a SCHEMA_ARRAY node.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null item_schema or allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_create_array" takes item_schema as Integer, min_items as Integer, max_items as Integer, unique_items as Integer returns Integer:
    If item_schema is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let payload be proc allocate from Layout with ARRAY_PAYLOAD_SIZE
    If payload is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with payload, 0, item_schema
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with payload, 8, min_items
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with payload, 16, max_items
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with payload, 24, unique_items
    Let node be proc schema_create with SCHEMA_ARRAY, payload
    If node is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with payload
        Return 0
    End If
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning
Convenience: build a SCHEMA_STRING with no constraints (any string).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Construct an empty StringConstraints and wrap.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_create_string_any" returns Integer:
    Let c be proc string_constraints_create with 0 minus 1, 0 minus 1, 0, FORMAT_NONE
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let n be proc schema_create with SCHEMA_STRING, c
    If n is equal to 0:
        proc string_constraints_destroy with c
        Return 0
    End If
    Return n
End Process

@Reasoning
Convenience: build a SCHEMA_INTEGER with no bounds (any integer).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Construct an empty IntegerConstraints and wrap.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_create_integer_any" returns Integer:
    Let c be proc integer_constraints_create with 0, 0, 0, 0, 0
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let n be proc schema_create with SCHEMA_INTEGER, c
    If n is equal to 0:
        proc integer_constraints_destroy with c
        Return 0
    End If
    Return n
End Process

@Reasoning
Convenience: build a SCHEMA_FLOAT with no bounds.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Construct an empty FloatConstraints and wrap.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_create_float_any" returns Integer:
    Let c be proc float_constraints_create with 0, 0, 0, 0, 0
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let n be proc schema_create with SCHEMA_FLOAT, c
    If n is equal to 0:
        proc float_constraints_destroy with c
        Return 0
    End If
    Return n
End Process

@Reasoning
Convenience: build a SCHEMA_BOOLEAN node (no parameters).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
schema_create with kind=BOOLEAN and payload=0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_create_boolean" returns Integer:
    Return proc schema_create with SCHEMA_BOOLEAN, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Convenience: build a SCHEMA_NULL node.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
schema_create with kind=NULL.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_create_null" returns Integer:
    Return proc schema_create with SCHEMA_NULL, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Convenience: build a SCHEMA_ANY node (matches every value).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
schema_create with kind=ANY.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
