Time: amortized O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null inputs or kind mismatch.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_composite_add_subschema" takes node as Integer, sub as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If sub is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 0
    Let ok be 0
    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_ALL_OF:
        Set ok to 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_ONE_OF:
        Set ok to 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_UNION:
        Set ok to 1
    End If
    If ok is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let lst be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 8
    If lst is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc list_push from List with lst, sub
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Get or allocate the per-object extras record at offset 32 of a
SCHEMA_OBJECT node. Returns the existing pointer or a fresh zeroed
record. Used by object-level keyword setters (additionalProperties,
dependentRequired, minProperties).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Read offset 32. If zero, allocate an OBJECT_EXTRAS_SIZE block and zero
every field. Store the pointer back at offset 32.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null node or allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_object_extras_get_or_create" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 0
    If kind is not equal to SCHEMA_OBJECT:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let extras be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 32
    If extras is not equal to 0:
        Return extras
    End If
    Set extras to proc allocate from Layout with OBJECT_EXTRAS_SIZE
    If extras is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with extras, 0, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with extras, 8, AP_POLICY_UNSET
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with extras, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with extras, 24, 0 minus 1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 32, extras
    Return extras
End Process

@Reasoning
Configure the additionalProperties keyword on a SCHEMA_OBJECT node.
Pass 0 for the "false" policy (reject any non-declared properties);
pass a SchemaNode pointer for the constrained policy (every extra
property must validate against the given subschema); the true policy
(allow any extras) is the default and need not be set explicitly.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Look up or create the object extras record; set the policy byte and
the subschema pointer. The subschema is adopted and freed on destroy.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null node, kind mismatch, or extras allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_object_set_additional_properties_false" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let extras be proc schema_object_extras_get_or_create with node
    If extras is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with extras, 0, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with extras, 8, AP_POLICY_FALSE
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Set the additionalProperties subschema. Any property in the value that
is not in the declared properties table must validate against this
subschema. The subschema is adopted.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Get-or-create extras and store the subschema and policy=schema.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null node or null subschema.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_object_set_additional_properties_schema" takes node as Integer, sub as Integer returns Integer:
    If sub is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let extras be proc schema_object_extras_get_or_create with node
    If extras is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with extras, 0, sub
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with extras, 8, AP_POLICY_SCHEMA
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Add a dependentRequired entry: when the named key is present in the
validated object, every name in dependents_list must also be present.
The dependents_list is adopted (List<String> of duplicated names) and
freed on schema_destroy.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Get-or-create extras. Initialize the dependent_required dictionary if
absent. Duplicate the key and store the list against it. Existing
entries for the same key are released first.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|key|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null inputs.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_object_add_dependent_required" takes node as Integer, key as Integer, dependents_list as Integer returns Integer:
    If key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If dependents_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let extras be proc schema_object_extras_get_or_create with node
    If extras is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let map be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with extras, 16
    If map is equal to 0:
        Set map to proc create from Dict
        If map is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with extras, 16, map
    End If
    Let prior be proc get from Dict with map, key
    If prior is not equal to 0:
        Let pn be proc list_length from List with prior
        Let pi be 0
        While pi is less than pn:
            Let s be proc list_get from List with prior, pi
            If s is not equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with s
            End If
            Set pi to pi plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with prior
    End If
    Note: Dict.set duplicates the key string internally.
    proc set from Dict with map, key, dependents_list
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Get or allocate the numeric (integer/float) extras record holding
