Note: ============================================================================
Note: DESTRUCTOR
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Recursively free a SchemaNode and all owned children. The destructor
inspects kind to decide which subtree to walk.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free title/description if present. Switch on kind:
  - OBJECT: walk field list, destroy each ObjectField, free list
  - ARRAY: recursively destroy payload schema
  - STRING: free StringConstraints
  - INTEGER: free IntegerConstraints
  - FLOAT: free FloatConstraints
  - UNION: walk variant list, destroy each, free list
  - REFERENCE: free name string
  - ENUM: walk value list, free each, free list
Then free the node record.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(s) where s is total subtree size. Space: O(d) recursion depth.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Safe to call with null (no-op).
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_destroy" takes n as Integer returns Integer:
    If n is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let title be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with n, 16
    If title is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with title
    End If
    Let desc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with n, 24
    If desc is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with desc
    End If
    Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with n, 0
    Let payload be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with n, 8

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_OBJECT:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let count be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let i be 0
            While i is less than count:
                Let f be proc list_get from List with payload, i
                If f is not equal to 0:
                    proc object_field_destroy with f
                End If
                Set i to i plus 1
            End While
            proc list_destroy from List with payload
        End If
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_ARRAY:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let item_schema_inner be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with payload, 0
            If item_schema_inner is not equal to 0:
                proc schema_destroy with item_schema_inner
            End If
            proc deallocate from Layout with payload
        End If
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_STRING:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            proc string_constraints_destroy with payload
        End If
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_INTEGER:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            proc integer_constraints_destroy with payload
        End If
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_FLOAT:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            proc float_constraints_destroy with payload
        End If
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_UNION:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let vcount be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let j be 0
            While j is less than vcount:
                Let v be proc list_get from List with payload, j
                If v is not equal to 0:
                    proc schema_destroy with v
                End If
                Set j to j plus 1
            End While
            proc list_destroy from List with payload
        End If
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_AND:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let acount be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let aj be 0
            While aj is less than acount:
                Let av be proc list_get from List with payload, aj
                If av is not equal to 0:
                    proc schema_destroy with av
                End If
                Set aj to aj plus 1
            End While
            proc list_destroy from List with payload
        End If
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_NOT:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let ncount be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let nj be 0
            While nj is less than ncount:
                Let nv be proc list_get from List with payload, nj
                If nv is not equal to 0:
                    proc schema_destroy with nv
                End If
                Set nj to nj plus 1
            End While
            proc list_destroy from List with payload
        End If
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_REFERENCE:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with payload
        End If
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_ENUM:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let ecount be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let k be 0
            While k is less than ecount:
                Let s be proc list_get from List with payload, k
                If s is not equal to 0:
                    proc deallocate from Layout with s
                End If
                Set k to k plus 1
            End While
            proc list_destroy from List with payload
        End If
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_ALL_OF:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let all_count be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let all_j be 0
            While all_j is less than all_count:
                Let all_v be proc list_get from List with payload, all_j
                If all_v is not equal to 0:
                    proc schema_destroy with all_v
                End If
                Set all_j to all_j plus 1
            End While
            proc list_destroy from List with payload
        End If
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_ONE_OF:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let one_count be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let one_j be 0
            While one_j is less than one_count:
                Let one_v be proc list_get from List with payload, one_j
                If one_v is not equal to 0:
                    proc schema_destroy with one_v
                End If
                Set one_j to one_j plus 1
            End While
            proc list_destroy from List with payload
        End If
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_CONST:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            proc config_value_destroy from Cfg with payload
        End If
    End If

    Let extras be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with n, 32
    If extras is not equal to 0:
        If kind is equal to SCHEMA_OBJECT:
            Let extra_sub be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with extras, 0
            If extra_sub is not equal to 0:
                proc schema_destroy with extra_sub
            End If
            Let dep_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with extras, 16
            If dep_map is not equal to 0:
                Note: Free the value lists first; Dict.destroy frees the
                Note: stored key strings on its own.
                Let dep_keys be proc keys from Dict with dep_map
                If dep_keys is not equal to 0:
                    Let dkc be proc list_length from List with dep_keys
                    Let dki be 0
                    While dki is less than dkc:
                        Let dkey be proc list_get from List with dep_keys, dki
                        If dkey is not equal to 0:
                            Let dval be proc get from Dict with dep_map, dkey
                            If dval is not equal to 0:
                                Let dvn be proc list_length from List with dval
                                Let dvi be 0
                                While dvi is less than dvn:
                                    Let dvs be proc list_get from List with dval, dvi
                                    If dvs is not equal to 0:
                                        proc deallocate from Layout with dvs
                                    End If
                                    Set dvi to dvi plus 1
                                End While
                                proc list_destroy from List with dval
                            End If
                        End If
                        Set dki to dki plus 1
                    End While
                    proc list_destroy from List with dep_keys
                End If
                proc destroy from Dict with dep_map
            End If
            proc deallocate from Layout with extras
        End If
        If kind is equal to SCHEMA_INTEGER:
            proc deallocate from Layout with extras
        End If
        If kind is equal to SCHEMA_FLOAT:
            proc deallocate from Layout with extras
        End If
        If kind is equal to SCHEMA_ARRAY:
            Let pref be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with extras, 0
            If pref is not equal to 0:
                Let pn be proc list_length from List with pref
                Let pix be 0
                While pix is less than pn:
                    Let ps be proc list_get from List with pref, pix
                    If ps is not equal to 0:
                        proc schema_destroy with ps
                    End If
                    Set pix to pix plus 1
                End While
                proc list_destroy from List with pref
            End If
            Let cont_sub be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with extras, 8
            If cont_sub is not equal to 0:
                proc schema_destroy with cont_sub
            End If
            proc deallocate from Layout with extras
        End If
    End If

    Let defs_reg be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with n, 40
    If defs_reg is not equal to 0:
        Note: Destroy each definition value; Dict.destroy frees keys.
        Let def_keys be proc keys from Dict with defs_reg
        If def_keys is not equal to 0:
            Let dkn be proc list_length from List with def_keys
            Let dki2 be 0
            While dki2 is less than dkn:
                Let dkey2 be proc list_get from List with def_keys, dki2
                If dkey2 is not equal to 0:
                    Let dsv be proc get from Dict with defs_reg, dkey2
                    If dsv is not equal to 0:
                        proc schema_destroy with dsv
                    End If
                End If
                Set dki2 to dki2 plus 1
            End While
            proc list_destroy from List with def_keys
        End If
        proc destroy from Dict with defs_reg
    End If

    proc deallocate from Layout with n
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: VALIDATION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Construct a ValidationIssue diagnostic record. The path is a JSON-pointer
style location (e.g. "/items/3/name"), the message is human readable, and
code is one of ERROR_*. Both strings are duplicated so the issue owns
them.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Duplicate path and message, allocate 24-byte record, store all three
fields.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|path|+|message|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "validation_issue_create" takes path as Integer, message as Integer, code as Integer returns Integer:
    Let pdup be 0
    If path is not equal to 0:
        Set pdup to proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with path
    End If
    Let mdup be 0
    If message is not equal to 0:
        Set mdup to proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with message
    End If
    Let issue be proc allocate from Layout with VALIDATION_ISSUE_SIZE
    If issue is equal to 0:
        If pdup is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with pdup
        End If
        If mdup is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with mdup
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with issue, 0, pdup
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with issue, 8, mdup
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with issue, 16, code
    Return issue
End Process

@Reasoning
Free a single ValidationIssue and its owned strings.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free path, message, then the record.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Safe to call with null.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "validation_issue_destroy" takes i as Integer returns Integer:
    If i is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let p be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with i, 0
    If p is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with p
    End If
    Let m be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with i, 8
    If m is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with m
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with i
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Free a list of ValidationIssue values, then the list itself.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Iterate, destroy each issue, then list_destroy.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Safe to call with null list.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "validation_issues_destroy" takes issues as Integer returns Integer:
    If issues is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc list_length from List with issues
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let entry be proc list_get from List with issues, i
        If entry is not equal to 0:
            proc validation_issue_destroy with entry
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc list_destroy from List with issues
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Read the issue path string.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "validation_issue_path" takes i as Integer returns Integer:
    If i is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with i, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Read the issue message string.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 8.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "validation_issue_message" takes i as Integer returns Integer:
    If i is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with i, 8
