@Reasoning
Read the issue error code.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 16.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "validation_issue_code" takes i as Integer returns Integer:
    If i is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with i, 16
End Process

@Reasoning
Append an issue to an issue list, growing the list as needed. Used by the
recursive walker.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
list_push.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: amortized O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null list.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "issues_append" takes issues as Integer, path as Integer, message as Integer, code as Integer returns Integer:
    If issues is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let issue be proc validation_issue_create with path, message, code
    If issue is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc list_push from List with issues, issue
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Structurally compare two ConfigValue trees. Two values are equal when
they have the same kind AND the same underlying data. CV_NULL is
trivially equal to CV_NULL; CV_BOOL/CV_INTEGER compare by integer value;
CV_STRING compares the underlying string contents; CV_LIST compares
element-by-element with cv_equals (positional); CV_MAP compares as
unordered key sets and, for each key, recursively compares values.

Two distinct CV_FLOAT-encoded numeric strings whose canonical numeric
value is identical do NOT compare equal here because the schema layer
preserves the original text for round-trip fidelity. Callers requiring
numeric equality across encodings must normalize before comparing.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Compare kinds first. Then per kind:
  - CV_NULL: equal.
  - CV_STRING: compare string contents.
  - CV_INTEGER: compare integer values.
  - CV_FLOAT: compare via string contents (the underlying CV_FLOAT shape
    is wrapped as CV_STRING in this codebase, so this branch is reached
    only if a future CV_FLOAT type is added).
  - CV_BOOL: compare bool values.
  - CV_LIST: same length, all elements pairwise equal.
  - CV_MAP: same key count, every key in one is in the other, and the
    associated values are pairwise equal.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over the smaller of the two trees. Space: O(d) recursion
depth.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 if either input is null and the other is not. Two null
pointers are not considered equal (no value).
@End Security_Scope
Process called "cv_equals" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ka be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with a
    Let kb be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with b
    If ka is not equal to kb:
        Return 0
    End If
    If ka is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    If ka is equal to 1:
        Let sa be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with a
        Let sb be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with b
        If sa is equal to 0:
            If sb is equal to 0:
                Return 1
            End If
            Return 0
        End If
        If sb is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return proc string_equals from StringCore with sa, sb
    End If
    If ka is equal to 2:
        Let ia be proc config_value_as_integer from Cfg with a
        Let ib be proc config_value_as_integer from Cfg with b
        If ia is equal to ib:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    If ka is equal to 3:
        Note: CV_FLOAT is currently surfaced as CV_STRING; fall back to
        Note: string equality on the underlying numeric text.
        Let fa be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with a
        Let fb be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with b
        If fa is equal to 0:
            If fb is equal to 0:
                Return 1
            End If
            Return 0
        End If
        If fb is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return proc string_equals from StringCore with fa, fb
    End If
    If ka is equal to 4:
        Let ba be proc config_value_as_bool from Cfg with a
        Let bb be proc config_value_as_bool from Cfg with b
        If ba is equal to bb:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    If ka is equal to 5:
        Let la be proc config_value_as_list from Cfg with a
        Let lb be proc config_value_as_list from Cfg with b
        If la is equal to 0:
            If lb is equal to 0:
                Return 1
            End If
            Return 0
        End If
        If lb is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let len_a be proc list_length from List with la
        Let len_b be proc list_length from List with lb
        If len_a is not equal to len_b:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let li be 0
        While li is less than len_a:
            Let ea be proc list_get from List with la, li
            Let eb be proc list_get from List with lb, li
            Let eq be proc cv_equals with ea, eb
            If eq is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            Set li to li plus 1
        End While
        Return 1
    End If
    If ka is equal to 6:
        Let ma be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with a
        Let mb be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with b
        If ma is equal to 0:
            If mb is equal to 0:
                Return 1
            End If
            Return 0
        End If
        If mb is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let keys_a be proc keys from Dict with ma
        Let keys_b be proc keys from Dict with mb
        Let count_a be proc list_length from List with keys_a
        Let count_b be proc list_length from List with keys_b
        If count_a is not equal to count_b:
            proc list_destroy from List with keys_a
            proc list_destroy from List with keys_b
            Return 0
        End If
        Let mi be 0
        Let map_eq be 1
        While mi is less than count_a:
            Let key be proc list_get from List with keys_a, mi
            Let va be proc get from Dict with ma, key
            Let vb be proc get from Dict with mb, key
            If vb is equal to 0:
                Set map_eq to 0
                Set mi to count_a
            Otherwise:
                Let veq be proc cv_equals with va, vb
                If veq is equal to 0:
                    Set map_eq to 0
                    Set mi to count_a
                End If
            End If
            Set mi to mi plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with keys_a
        proc list_destroy from List with keys_b
        Return map_eq
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Recursively validate a ConfigValue against a SchemaNode and append every
violation to the issues list. The path is the JSON-pointer-style location
of the current value. The result is the issues list (caller-owned).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Switch on schema kind:
  - ANY: accept everything.
  - NULL: accept iff CV_NULL.
  - BOOLEAN: accept iff CV_BOOL.
  - INTEGER: accept iff CV_INTEGER and integer-bounds satisfied.
  - FLOAT: accept iff CV_FLOAT (float bounds checked via float helpers in
           caller-extension; here we accept CV_FLOAT and skip bounds
           because Float values are pointers and bound checks require
           the runtime float compare in the consumer).
  - STRING: accept iff CV_STRING and length bounds satisfied. Pattern
           and format are recorded as not-yet-applicable: validation
           returns no error (regex engine is outside this module's
           scope; consumers must call json_schema for full coverage).
  - OBJECT: accept iff CV_MAP. For each declared field: if required and
           missing, emit ERROR_MISSING_FIELD; if present, recurse into
           the field's schema with extended path.
  - ARRAY: accept iff CV_LIST. Recurse into every element using the
           item schema.
  - UNION: accept iff at least one variant validates with zero issues.
           If none match, emit ERROR_UNION_NO_MATCH.
  - REFERENCE: emit ERROR_REFERENCE_UNRESOLVED (registry resolution
           lives in higher-layer modules like json_schema).
  - ENUM: accept iff CV_STRING and value appears in the enum list.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over the (value, schema) pair. Space: O(d) recursion depth.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns the issues list. Never null on success even if no issues are
found - it will simply be empty. Caller owns and must destroy via
validation_issues_destroy.
@End Security_Scope
@Reasoning
Apply a JSON Schema "format" assertion to a string value. Returns 1 if
the value satisfies the format, 0 otherwise. Each format delegates to
the dedicated primitive parser (uuid_from_string, ipv4_from_string,
ipv6_from_string, url_parse, date_parse_iso_8601, time_of_day_parse_iso_8601)
so that the same parsing semantics already covered by primitive tests
gate schema validation.

Supported formats (FORMAT_* constants):
  - FORMAT_EMAIL: local-part "@" domain with at least one '.' in domain
    and no whitespace or control characters.
  - FORMAT_URL / FORMAT_URI / FORMAT_URI_REFERENCE: parsed by url_parse.
    URI-reference is permissive: relative references with no scheme
    succeed iff parsing returns a valid object OR the string is non-empty
    and contains no control characters.
  - FORMAT_UUID: uuid_from_string returns non-null on success.
  - FORMAT_DATE: date_parse_iso_8601 returns a non-negative pointer.
  - FORMAT_TIME: time_of_day_parse_iso_8601 returns a non-negative
    pointer over the entire string.
  - FORMAT_DATE_TIME: 10-byte date prefix + 'T' + remainder valid as
    time-of-day. Trailing 'Z' or numeric offset is permitted.
  - FORMAT_IPV4 / FORMAT_IPV6: corresponding from_string primitives
    return non-zero on success.
  - FORMAT_REGEX: regex_compile must accept the pattern.
  - FORMAT_HOSTNAME: validated as labels separated by '.' with each label
    containing only ASCII alphanumerics or '-' and not starting/ending
    with '-'. Total length <= 253, label length <= 63.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Switch on the FORMAT_* constant. Allocate the parser's output, check
return code, then free the output. For email and hostname the validation
is performed inline because no general-purpose parser is exposed.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over value length. No allocations escape the function.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 for unknown formats and null inputs. Each delegated parser is
length-bounded.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "format_validate" takes value as Integer, format as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If format is equal to FORMAT_NONE:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let vlen be proc string_length from StringCore with value
    If vlen is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If format is equal to FORMAT_UUID:
        Let u be proc uuid_from_string from UUID with value
        If u is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc uuid_destroy from UUID with u
        Return 1
    End If

    If format is equal to FORMAT_IPV4:
        Let a4 be proc ipv4_from_string from IPv4 with value
        If a4 is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc deallocate from Layout with a4
        Return 1
    End If

    If format is equal to FORMAT_IPV6:
        Let a6 be proc ipv6_from_string from IPv6 with value
        If a6 is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc ipv6_destroy from IPv6 with a6
        Return 1
    End If

    If format is equal to FORMAT_URL:
        Let u_url be proc url_parse from URL with value
        If u_url is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc url_destroy from URL with u_url
        Return 1
    End If

    If format is equal to FORMAT_URI:
        Let u_uri be proc url_parse from URL with value
        If u_uri is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc url_destroy from URL with u_uri
        Return 1
    End If

    If format is equal to FORMAT_URI_REFERENCE:
        Let u_ref be proc url_parse from URL with value
        If u_ref is not equal to 0:
            proc url_destroy from URL with u_ref
            Return 1
        End If
        Note: A URI-reference may be a relative reference (no scheme).
        Note: Accept any non-empty string with no ASCII control chars.
        Let i_uref be 0
        Let bad_uref be 0
        While i_uref is less than vlen:
            Let ch_uref be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with value, i_uref
            If ch_uref is less than 32:
                Set bad_uref to 1
            End If
            If ch_uref is equal to 127:
                Set bad_uref to 1
            End If
            Set i_uref to i_uref plus 1
        End While
        If bad_uref is equal to 1:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If format is equal to FORMAT_DATE:
        Let d be proc date_parse_iso_8601 from Date with value
        If d is less than 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc deallocate from Layout with d
        Return 1
    End If

    If format is equal to FORMAT_TIME:
        Let t be proc time_of_day_parse_iso_8601 from TOD with value, vlen
        If t is less than 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Note: The parser allocates a TimeOfDay record; release it.
        proc deallocate from Layout with t
        Return 1
    End If

    If format is equal to FORMAT_DATE_TIME:
        If vlen is less than 11:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let sep be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with value, 10
        Let sep_ok be 0
        If sep is equal to 84:
            Set sep_ok to 1
        End If
        If sep is equal to 116:
            Set sep_ok to 1
        End If
        If sep is equal to 32:
            Set sep_ok to 1
        End If
        If sep_ok is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let date_buf be proc allocate from Layout with 11
        If date_buf is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let di be 0
        While di is less than 10:
            Let dc be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with value, di
            proc memory_set_byte from Memory with date_buf, di, dc
            Set di to di plus 1
        End While
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with date_buf, 10, 0
        Let d2 be proc date_parse_iso_8601 from Date with date_buf
        proc deallocate from Layout with date_buf
        If d2 is less than 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc deallocate from Layout with d2
        Note: Validate the time portion after the separator. Strip any
        Note: trailing timezone suffix ("Z" or "+HH:MM" / "-HH:MM").
        Let time_start be 11
        Let time_end be vlen
        If time_end is greater than time_start:
            Let last_idx be time_end minus 1
            Let last_ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with value, last_idx
            If last_ch is equal to 90:
                Set time_end to time_end minus 1
            End If
            If last_ch is equal to 122:
                Set time_end to time_end minus 1
            End If
        End If
        Let tz_pos be 0 minus 1
        Let tj be time_start
        While tj is less than time_end:
            Let tch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with value, tj
            If tch is equal to 43:
                Set tz_pos to tj
            End If
            If tch is equal to 45:
                Set tz_pos to tj
            End If
            Set tj to tj plus 1
        End While
        If tz_pos is greater than or equal to 0:
            Set time_end to tz_pos
        End If
        Let tlen be time_end minus time_start
        If tlen is less than or equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let time_buf be proc allocate from Layout with tlen plus 1
        If time_buf is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let ti be 0
        While ti is less than tlen:
            Let tcb be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with value, time_start plus ti
            proc memory_set_byte from Memory with time_buf, ti, tcb
            Set ti to ti plus 1
        End While
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with time_buf, tlen, 0
        Let t2 be proc time_of_day_parse_iso_8601 from TOD with time_buf, tlen
        proc deallocate from Layout with time_buf
        If t2 is less than 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc deallocate from Layout with t2
        Return 1
    End If

    If format is equal to FORMAT_REGEX:
        Let r be proc regex_compile from Regex with value, 0
        If r is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc deallocate from Layout with r
        Return 1
    End If

    If format is equal to FORMAT_EMAIL:
        Let at_pos be 0 minus 1
        Let ei be 0
        Let ebad be 0
        While ei is less than vlen:
            Let ech be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with value, ei
            If ech is equal to 64:
                If at_pos is equal to (0 minus 1):
                    Set at_pos to ei
                Otherwise:
                    Set ebad to 1
                End If
            End If
            If ech is less than 33:
                Set ebad to 1
            End If
            If ech is equal to 127:
                Set ebad to 1
            End If
            Set ei to ei plus 1
        End While
        If ebad is equal to 1:
            Return 0
        End If
        If at_pos is less than 1:
            Return 0
        End If
        If at_pos is greater than or equal to (vlen minus 1):
            Return 0
        End If
        Let dot_seen be 0
        Let dpi be at_pos plus 1
        While dpi is less than vlen:
            Let dch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with value, dpi
            If dch is equal to 46:
                If dpi is greater than (at_pos plus 1):
                    If dpi is less than (vlen minus 1):
                        Set dot_seen to 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
            Set dpi to dpi plus 1
        End While
        If dot_seen is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If format is equal to FORMAT_HOSTNAME:
        If vlen is greater than 253:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let h_i be 0
        Let label_len be 0
        Let label_start_ok be 0
        Let label_last_ch be 0
        Let h_bad be 0
        While h_i is less than vlen:
            Let h_ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with value, h_i
            If h_ch is equal to 46:
                If label_len is equal to 0:
                    Set h_bad to 1
                End If
                If label_last_ch is equal to 45:
                    Set h_bad to 1
                End If
                Set label_len to 0
                Set label_start_ok to 0
            Otherwise:
                Let is_alpha be 0
                If h_ch is greater than or equal to 65:
                    If h_ch is less than or equal to 90:
                        Set is_alpha to 1
                    End If
                End If
                If h_ch is greater than or equal to 97:
                    If h_ch is less than or equal to 122:
                        Set is_alpha to 1
                    End If
                End If
                Let is_digit be 0
                If h_ch is greater than or equal to 48:
                    If h_ch is less than or equal to 57:
                        Set is_digit to 1
                    End If
                End If
                Let is_hyphen be 0
                If h_ch is equal to 45:
                    Set is_hyphen to 1
                End If
                If is_alpha is equal to 0:
                    If is_digit is equal to 0:
                        If is_hyphen is equal to 0:
                            Set h_bad to 1
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
                If label_len is equal to 0:
                    If is_hyphen is equal to 1:
                        Set h_bad to 1
                    End If
                    Set label_start_ok to 1
                End If
                Set label_len to label_len plus 1
                If label_len is greater than 63:
                    Set h_bad to 1
                End If
                Set label_last_ch to h_ch
            End If
            Set h_i to h_i plus 1
        End While
        If label_len is equal to 0:
            Set h_bad to 1
        End If
        If label_last_ch is equal to 45:
            Set h_bad to 1
        End If
        If h_bad is equal to 1:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: For format constants outside the supported set, accept the
    Note: string. JSON Schema treats format as a vocabulary that may be
    Note: open-ended; unknown formats are not validation failures.
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "schema_validate" takes value as Integer, schema as Integer returns Integer:
    Let issues be proc list_create from List
    If issues is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let root be 0
    Let slash be 0
    Let defs be 0
    If schema is not equal to 0:
        Set defs to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with schema, 40
    End If
    proc validate_walk_with_defs with value, schema, root, slash, issues, defs
    Return issues
End Process

@Reasoning
Internal recursive validator. The path argument is the dotted-pointer
path for diagnostic messages. Each recursion may allocate a temporary
extended path which is freed at the end of the branch.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Inspect schema kind via memory_get_int64. Apply per-kind validation logic
exactly as documented in schema_validate.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(s) where s is subtree size; per-step constant work.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper. Caller-supplied path may be null (treated as root).
@End Security_Scope
Process called "validate_walk" takes value as Integer, schema as Integer, path as Integer, indent as Integer, issues as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc validate_walk_with_defs with value, schema, path, indent, issues, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Full validator implementation parameterized by a $defs registry so
SCHEMA_REFERENCE nodes can be resolved during recursion. The registry
is a dictionary mapping definition names to SchemaNode pointers as
populated by schema_add_definition.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Identical to validate_walk's per-kind branch table plus
  - SCHEMA_ALL_OF: every subschema must yield zero probe issues.
  - SCHEMA_ONE_OF: exactly one subschema must yield zero probe issues.
  - SCHEMA_CONST: cv_equals against the const value.
  - SCHEMA_REFERENCE: look up name in defs registry; on success
    recurse into the referenced schema (with infinite-recursion guard
    via depth limit); on failure emit ERROR_REFERENCE_UNRESOLVED.
  - SCHEMA_INTEGER / SCHEMA_FLOAT: also test the exclusiveMin/Max
    bounds stored in the numeric extras record.
  - SCHEMA_OBJECT: also enforce additionalProperties and
    dependentRequired stored in the object extras record.
  - SCHEMA_ARRAY: also apply prefixItems positional schemas and the
    contains subschema stored in the array extras record.
The indent parameter doubles as a recursion-depth tracker for $ref
resolution; an absolute cap of 64 stops pathological self-referential
schemas from blowing the stack.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(s) over the (value, schema) pair. Space: O(d) recursion depth.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper. defs may be 0 (no registry available); SCHEMA_REFERENCE
nodes still report unresolved in that case.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "validate_walk_with_defs" takes value as Integer, schema as Integer, path as Integer, indent as Integer, issues as Integer, defs as Integer returns Integer:
    If schema is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If indent is greater than 64:
        proc issues_append with issues, path, "schema recursion depth exceeded", ERROR_REFERENCE_UNRESOLVED
        Return 1
    End If
    Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with schema, 0
    Let payload be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with schema, 8

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_ANY:
        Return 1
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_NULL:
        Let vk be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with value
        If vk is not equal to 0:
            proc issues_append with issues, path, "expected null", ERROR_TYPE_MISMATCH
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_BOOLEAN:
        Let vk2 be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with value
        If vk2 is not equal to 4:
            proc issues_append with issues, path, "expected boolean", ERROR_TYPE_MISMATCH
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_INTEGER:
        Let vk3 be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with value
        If vk3 is not equal to 2:
            proc issues_append with issues, path, "expected integer", ERROR_TYPE_MISMATCH
            Return 1
        End If
        Let iv be proc config_value_as_integer from Cfg with value
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let has_min be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with payload, 0
            If has_min is equal to 1:
                Let mn be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with payload, 8
                If iv is less than mn:
                    proc issues_append with issues, path, "integer below minimum", ERROR_MIN_VALUE
                End If
            End If
            Let has_max be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with payload, 16
            If has_max is equal to 1:
                Let mx be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with payload, 24
                If iv is greater than mx:
                    proc issues_append with issues, path, "integer above maximum", ERROR_MAX_VALUE
                End If
            End If
            Let mof be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with payload, 32
            If mof is not equal to 0:
                Let r be iv minus ((iv divided by mof) multiplied by mof)
                If r is not equal to 0:
                    proc issues_append with issues, path, "integer not multiple of base", ERROR_MULTIPLE_OF
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Let int_extras be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with schema, 32
        If int_extras is not equal to 0:
            Let exmin_set be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with int_extras, 8
            If exmin_set is equal to 1:
                Let exmin_v be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with int_extras, 0
                If iv is less than or equal to exmin_v:
                    proc issues_append with issues, path, "integer not strictly greater than exclusiveMinimum", ERROR_MIN_VALUE
                End If
            End If
            Let exmax_set be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with int_extras, 24
            If exmax_set is equal to 1:
                Let exmax_v be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with int_extras, 16
                If iv is greater than or equal to exmax_v:
                    proc issues_append with issues, path, "integer not strictly less than exclusiveMaximum", ERROR_MAX_VALUE
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_FLOAT:
        Let vkf be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with value
        Let cv_int_for_float be 0
        Let v_is_int be 0
        Let v_is_float be 0
        If vkf is equal to 2:
            Set v_is_int to 1
            Set cv_int_for_float to proc config_value_as_integer from Cfg with value
        End If
        If vkf is equal to 3:
            Set v_is_float to 1
        End If
        If v_is_int is equal to 0:
            If v_is_float is equal to 0:
                proc issues_append with issues, path, "expected number", ERROR_TYPE_MISMATCH
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
        Let flt_extras be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with schema, 32
        If flt_extras is not equal to 0:
            If v_is_int is equal to 1:
                Let fxmin_set be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with flt_extras, 8
                If fxmin_set is equal to 1:
                    Let fxmin_v be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with flt_extras, 0
                    If cv_int_for_float is less than or equal to fxmin_v:
                        proc issues_append with issues, path, "number not strictly greater than exclusiveMinimum", ERROR_MIN_VALUE
                    End If
                End If
                Let fxmax_set be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with flt_extras, 24
                If fxmax_set is equal to 1:
                    Let fxmax_v be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with flt_extras, 16
                    If cv_int_for_float is greater than or equal to fxmax_v:
                        proc issues_append with issues, path, "number not strictly less than exclusiveMaximum", ERROR_MAX_VALUE
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_STRING:
        Let vks be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with value
        If vks is not equal to 1:
            proc issues_append with issues, path, "expected string", ERROR_TYPE_MISMATCH
            Return 1
        End If
        Let sptr be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with value
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            If sptr is not equal to 0:
                Let slen be proc string_length from StringCore with sptr
                Let mnlen be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with payload, 0
                If mnlen is greater than or equal to 0:
                    If slen is less than mnlen:
                        proc issues_append with issues, path, "string below min length", ERROR_MIN_LENGTH
                    End If
                End If
                Let mxlen be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with payload, 8
                If mxlen is greater than or equal to 0:
                    If slen is greater than mxlen:
                        proc issues_append with issues, path, "string above max length", ERROR_MAX_LENGTH
                    End If
                End If
                Let pat_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with payload, 16
                If pat_ptr is not equal to 0:
                    Let re be proc regex_compile from Regex with pat_ptr, 0
                    If re is equal to 0:
                        proc issues_append with issues, path, "string pattern is invalid regex", ERROR_PATTERN
                    Otherwise:
                        Let mres be proc regex_match from Regex with re, sptr
                        If mres is equal to 0:
                            proc issues_append with issues, path, "string does not match pattern", ERROR_PATTERN
                        Otherwise:
                            proc regex_match_destroy from Regex with mres
                        End If
                        proc deallocate from Layout with re
                    End If
                End If
                Let fmt_code be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with payload, 24
                If fmt_code is not equal to FORMAT_NONE:
                    Let ok_fmt be proc format_validate with sptr, fmt_code
                    If ok_fmt is equal to 0:
                        proc issues_append with issues, path, "string fails format constraint", ERROR_FORMAT
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_ARRAY:
        Let vka be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with value
        If vka is not equal to 5:
            proc issues_append with issues, path, "expected array", ERROR_TYPE_MISMATCH
            Return 1
        End If
        Let arr be proc config_value_as_list from Cfg with value
        Let prefix_count be 0
        Let arr_extras be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with schema, 32
        Let prefix_list be 0
        Let contains_sub be 0
        If arr_extras is not equal to 0:
            Set prefix_list to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with arr_extras, 0
            Set contains_sub to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with arr_extras, 8
            If prefix_list is not equal to 0:
                Set prefix_count to proc list_length from List with prefix_list
            End If
        End If
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let item_schema be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with payload, 0
            Let min_items be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with payload, 8
            Let max_items be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with payload, 16
            Let unique_items be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with payload, 24
            If arr is not equal to 0:
                Let ac be proc list_length from List with arr
                If min_items is greater than or equal to 0:
                    If ac is less than min_items:
                        proc issues_append with issues, path, "array below minItems", ERROR_MIN_VALUE
                    End If
                End If
                If max_items is greater than or equal to 0:
                    If ac is greater than max_items:
                        proc issues_append with issues, path, "array above maxItems", ERROR_MAX_VALUE
                    End If
                End If
                If unique_items is equal to 1:
                    Let ui be 0
                    Let dup_found be 0
                    While ui is less than ac:
                        Let uj be ui plus 1
                        While uj is less than ac:
                            Let ea be proc list_get from List with arr, ui
                            Let eb be proc list_get from List with arr, uj
                            Let cveq be proc cv_equals with ea, eb
                            If cveq is equal to 1:
                                Set dup_found to 1
                                Set uj to ac
                                Set ui to ac
                            End If
                            Set uj to uj plus 1
                        End While
                        Set ui to ui plus 1
                    End While
                    If dup_found is equal to 1:
                        proc issues_append with issues, path, "array elements not unique", ERROR_ENUM_VIOLATION
                    End If
                End If
                Note: Apply prefixItems for positions 0..prefix_count.
                If prefix_count is greater than 0:
                    Let p_i be 0
                    Let p_limit be prefix_count
                    If ac is less than p_limit:
                        Set p_limit to ac
                    End If
                    While p_i is less than p_limit:
                        Let p_elem be proc list_get from List with arr, p_i
                        Let p_sch be proc list_get from List with prefix_list, p_i
                        proc validate_walk_with_defs with p_elem, p_sch, path, indent plus 1, issues, defs
                        Set p_i to p_i plus 1
                    End While
                End If
                Note: Apply items_schema only to elements beyond the prefix range.
                If item_schema is not equal to 0:
                    Let i be prefix_count
                    While i is less than ac:
                        Let elem be proc list_get from List with arr, i
                        proc validate_walk_with_defs with elem, item_schema, path, indent plus 1, issues, defs
                        Set i to i plus 1
                    End While
                End If
                Note: Apply contains: at least one element must validate.
                If contains_sub is not equal to 0:
                    Let c_i be 0
                    Let any_contains be 0
                    While c_i is less than ac:
                        Let c_elem be proc list_get from List with arr, c_i
                        Let c_probe be proc list_create from List
                        If c_probe is not equal to 0:
                            proc validate_walk_with_defs with c_elem, contains_sub, path, indent plus 1, c_probe, defs
                            Let c_count be proc list_length from List with c_probe
                            If c_count is equal to 0:
                                Set any_contains to 1
                            End If
                            proc validation_issues_destroy with c_probe
                        End If
                        Set c_i to c_i plus 1
                    End While
                    If any_contains is equal to 0:
                        proc issues_append with issues, path, "no array element matches contains subschema", ERROR_UNION_NO_MATCH
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        Otherwise:
            Note: No primary payload but possibly prefix/contains extras.
            If arr is not equal to 0:
                Let ac2 be proc list_length from List with arr
                If prefix_count is greater than 0:
                    Let p2_i be 0
                    Let p2_limit be prefix_count
                    If ac2 is less than p2_limit:
                        Set p2_limit to ac2
                    End If
                    While p2_i is less than p2_limit:
                        Let p2_elem be proc list_get from List with arr, p2_i
                        Let p2_sch be proc list_get from List with prefix_list, p2_i
                        proc validate_walk_with_defs with p2_elem, p2_sch, path, indent plus 1, issues, defs
                        Set p2_i to p2_i plus 1
                    End While
                End If
                If contains_sub is not equal to 0:
                    Let c2_i be 0
                    Let any_contains2 be 0
                    While c2_i is less than ac2:
                        Let c2_elem be proc list_get from List with arr, c2_i
                        Let c2_probe be proc list_create from List
                        If c2_probe is not equal to 0:
                            proc validate_walk_with_defs with c2_elem, contains_sub, path, indent plus 1, c2_probe, defs
                            Let c2_count be proc list_length from List with c2_probe
                            If c2_count is equal to 0:
                                Set any_contains2 to 1
                            End If
                            proc validation_issues_destroy with c2_probe
                        End If
                        Set c2_i to c2_i plus 1
                    End While
                    If any_contains2 is equal to 0:
                        proc issues_append with issues, path, "no array element matches contains subschema", ERROR_UNION_NO_MATCH
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_OBJECT:
        Let vko be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with value
        If vko is not equal to 6:
            proc issues_append with issues, path, "expected object", ERROR_TYPE_MISMATCH
            Return 1
        End If
        Let dict be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with value
        Note: Walk declared properties first; collect declared names so
        Note: extras logic can identify additional properties later.
        Let declared be proc create from Dict
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let count be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let i2 be 0
            While i2 is less than count:
                Let fld be proc list_get from List with payload, i2
                If fld is not equal to 0:
                    Let fname be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with fld, 0
                    Let fschema be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with fld, 8
                    Let freq be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with fld, 16
                    If declared is not equal to 0:
                        If fname is not equal to 0:
                            proc set from Dict with declared, fname, fld
                        End If
                    End If
                    If dict is not equal to 0:
                        Let fv be proc get from Dict with dict, fname
                        If fv is equal to 0:
                            If freq is equal to 1:
                                proc issues_append with issues, path, "missing required field", ERROR_MISSING_FIELD
                            End If
                        Otherwise:
                            proc validate_walk_with_defs with fv, fschema, fname, indent plus 1, issues, defs
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
                Set i2 to i2 plus 1
            End While
        End If
        Note: additionalProperties + dependentRequired live in extras.
        Let obj_extras be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with schema, 32
        If obj_extras is not equal to 0:
            Let ap_sub be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with obj_extras, 0
            Let ap_policy be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with obj_extras, 8
            Let dep_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with obj_extras, 16
            If dict is not equal to 0:
                If ap_policy is not equal to AP_POLICY_UNSET:
                    If ap_policy is not equal to AP_POLICY_TRUE:
                        Let actual_keys be proc keys from Dict with dict
                        If actual_keys is not equal to 0:
                            Let ak_count be proc list_length from List with actual_keys
                            Let ak_i be 0
                            While ak_i is less than ak_count:
                                Let actual_key be proc list_get from List with actual_keys, ak_i
                                If actual_key is not equal to 0:
                                    Let declared_entry be 0
                                    If declared is not equal to 0:
                                        Set declared_entry to proc get from Dict with declared, actual_key
                                    End If
                                    If declared_entry is equal to 0:
                                        Let ap_value be proc get from Dict with dict, actual_key
                                        If ap_policy is equal to AP_POLICY_FALSE:
                                            proc issues_append with issues, actual_key, "unexpected additional property", ERROR_MISSING_FIELD
                                        End If
                                        If ap_policy is equal to AP_POLICY_SCHEMA:
                                            If ap_sub is not equal to 0:
                                                proc validate_walk_with_defs with ap_value, ap_sub, actual_key, indent plus 1, issues, defs
                                            End If
                                        End If
                                    End If
                                End If
                                Set ak_i to ak_i plus 1
                            End While
                            proc list_destroy from List with actual_keys
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
                If dep_map is not equal to 0:
                    Let dep_keys be proc keys from Dict with dep_map
                    If dep_keys is not equal to 0:
                        Let dk_count be proc list_length from List with dep_keys
                        Let dk_i be 0
                        While dk_i is less than dk_count:
                            Let dep_key be proc list_get from List with dep_keys, dk_i
                            If dep_key is not equal to 0:
                                Let trigger_present be proc contains from Dict with dict, dep_key
                                If trigger_present is equal to 1:
                                    Let req_list be proc get from Dict with dep_map, dep_key
                                    If req_list is not equal to 0:
                                        Let rln be proc list_length from List with req_list
                                        Let rli be 0
                                        While rli is less than rln:
                                            Let needed be proc list_get from List with req_list, rli
                                            If needed is not equal to 0:
                                                Let needed_present be proc contains from Dict with dict, needed
                                                If needed_present is equal to 0:
                                                    proc issues_append with issues, path, "dependentRequired property missing", ERROR_MISSING_FIELD
                                                End If
                                            End If
                                            Set rli to rli plus 1
                                        End While
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                            Set dk_i to dk_i plus 1
                        End While
                        proc list_destroy from List with dep_keys
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        If declared is not equal to 0:
            proc destroy from Dict with declared
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_UNION:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let vcount be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let any_match be 0
            Let j be 0
            While j is less than vcount:
                Let variant be proc list_get from List with payload, j
                Let probe be proc list_create from List
                If probe is not equal to 0:
                    proc validate_walk_with_defs with value, variant, path, indent plus 1, probe, defs
                    Let pcount be proc list_length from List with probe
                    If pcount is equal to 0:
                        Set any_match to 1
                    End If
                    proc validation_issues_destroy with probe
                End If
                Set j to j plus 1
            End While
            If any_match is equal to 0:
                proc issues_append with issues, path, "no union variant matched", ERROR_UNION_NO_MATCH
            End If
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_AND:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let acount be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let aj be 0
            While aj is less than acount:
                Let avar be proc list_get from List with payload, aj
                Let aprobe be proc list_create from List
                If aprobe is not equal to 0:
                    proc validate_walk_with_defs with value, avar, path, indent plus 1, aprobe, defs
                    Let apcount be proc list_length from List with aprobe
                    If apcount is greater than 0:
                        proc issues_append with issues, path, "AND conjunct did not match", ERROR_UNION_NO_MATCH
                    End If
                    proc validation_issues_destroy with aprobe
                End If
                Set aj to aj plus 1
            End While
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_NOT:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let ncount be proc list_length from List with payload
            If ncount is greater than 0:
                Let inner be proc list_get from List with payload, 0
                Let nprobe be proc list_create from List
                If nprobe is not equal to 0:
                    proc validate_walk_with_defs with value, inner, path, indent plus 1, nprobe, defs
                    Let npcount be proc list_length from List with nprobe
                    If npcount is equal to 0:
                        proc issues_append with issues, path, "value matched a NOT schema", ERROR_UNION_NO_MATCH
                    End If
                    proc validation_issues_destroy with nprobe
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_ALL_OF:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let allcount be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let allj be 0
            While allj is less than allcount:
                Let allvar be proc list_get from List with payload, allj
                Let allprobe be proc list_create from List
                If allprobe is not equal to 0:
                    proc validate_walk_with_defs with value, allvar, path, indent plus 1, allprobe, defs
                    Let allpc be proc list_length from List with allprobe
                    If allpc is greater than 0:
                        proc issues_append with issues, path, "allOf subschema did not match", ERROR_UNION_NO_MATCH
                    End If
                    proc validation_issues_destroy with allprobe
                End If
                Set allj to allj plus 1
            End While
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_ONE_OF:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let onecount be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let match_count be 0
            Let onej be 0
            While onej is less than onecount:
                Let onevar be proc list_get from List with payload, onej
                Let oneprobe be proc list_create from List
                If oneprobe is not equal to 0:
                    proc validate_walk_with_defs with value, onevar, path, indent plus 1, oneprobe, defs
                    Let onepc be proc list_length from List with oneprobe
                    If onepc is equal to 0:
                        Set match_count to match_count plus 1
                    End If
                    proc validation_issues_destroy with oneprobe
                End If
                Set onej to onej plus 1
            End While
            If match_count is equal to 0:
                proc issues_append with issues, path, "oneOf matched no subschema", ERROR_UNION_NO_MATCH
            End If
            If match_count is greater than 1:
                proc issues_append with issues, path, "oneOf matched more than one subschema", ERROR_UNION_NO_MATCH
            End If
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_CONST:
        Let const_eq be proc cv_equals with value, payload
        If const_eq is equal to 0:
            proc issues_append with issues, path, "value does not match const", ERROR_ENUM_VIOLATION
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_REFERENCE:
        If defs is equal to 0:
            proc issues_append with issues, path, "unresolved schema reference", ERROR_REFERENCE_UNRESOLVED
            Return 1
        End If
        Let resolved be proc schema_lookup_definition with defs, payload
        If resolved is equal to 0:
            proc issues_append with issues, path, "unresolved schema reference", ERROR_REFERENCE_UNRESOLVED
            Return 1
        End If
        proc validate_walk_with_defs with value, resolved, path, indent plus 1, issues, defs
        Return 1
    End If

    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_ENUM:
        Let vke be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with value
        If vke is not equal to 1:
            proc issues_append with issues, path, "enum value must be string", ERROR_TYPE_MISMATCH
            Return 1
        End If
        Let sval be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with value
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let ecount be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let k be 0
            Let matched be 0
            While k is less than ecount:
                Let candidate be proc list_get from List with payload, k
                If candidate is not equal to 0:
                    If sval is not equal to 0:
                        Let eq be proc string_equals from StringCore with sval, candidate
                        If eq is equal to 1:
                            Set matched to 1
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
                Set k to k plus 1
            End While
            If matched is equal to 0:
                proc issues_append with issues, path, "value not in enum", ERROR_ENUM_VIOLATION
            End If
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: WALKER
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Apply a callback to every node in a schema tree (pre-order). The callback
receives the node pointer and a caller-supplied state pointer. If the
callback returns 0, the walk terminates early.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Visit the current node first; if the callback returns 0, stop. Otherwise
recurse into structural children according to kind.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(s) over the subtree.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 1 if the walk completed, 0 if the callback aborted.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_walk" takes node as Integer, visitor as Integer, state as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    If visitor is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let cont be proc __builtin_call_indirect_2 from Builtins with visitor, node, state
    If cont is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 0
    Let payload be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 8
    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_OBJECT:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let count be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let i be 0
            While i is less than count:
                Let fld be proc list_get from List with payload, i
                If fld is not equal to 0:
                    Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with fld, 8
                    Let ok be proc schema_walk with child, visitor, state
                    If ok is equal to 0:
                        Return 0
                    End If
                End If
                Set i to i plus 1
            End While
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_ARRAY:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let item_schema_walk be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with payload, 0
            If item_schema_walk is not equal to 0:
                Let ok2 be proc schema_walk with item_schema_walk, visitor, state
                If ok2 is equal to 0:
                    Return 0
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_UNION:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let vcount be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let j be 0
            While j is less than vcount:
                Let variant be proc list_get from List with payload, j
                If variant is not equal to 0:
                    Let ok3 be proc schema_walk with variant, visitor, state
                    If ok3 is equal to 0:
                        Return 0
                    End If
                End If
                Set j to j plus 1
            End While
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_AND:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let acount be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let aj be 0
            While aj is less than acount:
                Let avar be proc list_get from List with payload, aj
                If avar is not equal to 0:
                    Let ok_a be proc schema_walk with avar, visitor, state
                    If ok_a is equal to 0:
                        Return 0
                    End If
                End If
                Set aj to aj plus 1
            End While
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_NOT:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let ncount be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let nj be 0
            While nj is less than ncount:
                Let nvar be proc list_get from List with payload, nj
                If nvar is not equal to 0:
                    Let ok_n be proc schema_walk with nvar, visitor, state
                    If ok_n is equal to 0:
                        Return 0
                    End If
                End If
                Set nj to nj plus 1
            End While
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_ALL_OF:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let walk_all_count be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let walk_all_j be 0
            While walk_all_j is less than walk_all_count:
                Let walk_all_var be proc list_get from List with payload, walk_all_j
                If walk_all_var is not equal to 0:
                    Let ok_all be proc schema_walk with walk_all_var, visitor, state
                    If ok_all is equal to 0:
                        Return 0
                    End If
                End If
                Set walk_all_j to walk_all_j plus 1
            End While
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_ONE_OF:
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let walk_one_count be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let walk_one_j be 0
            While walk_one_j is less than walk_one_count:
                Let walk_one_var be proc list_get from List with payload, walk_one_j
                If walk_one_var is not equal to 0:
                    Let ok_one be proc schema_walk with walk_one_var, visitor, state
                    If ok_one is equal to 0:
                        Return 0
                    End If
                End If
                Set walk_one_j to walk_one_j plus 1
            End While
        End If
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: COMPOSITION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Compose two schemas using AND, OR, or NOT semantics. Each operator
produces a distinct node kind so the validator can apply the correct
boolean semantics:

  - COMPOSE_AND -> SCHEMA_AND node holding a two-element variant list.
    Validation requires both variants to match.
  - COMPOSE_OR  -> SCHEMA_UNION node holding a two-element variant list.
    Validation requires at least one variant to match (anyOf).
  - COMPOSE_NOT -> SCHEMA_NOT node holding a one-element variant list.
    Validation requires the wrapped schema to fail.

Variant lists are shared with the standard SCHEMA_UNION layout so
schema_walk, schema_destroy, and serialization can treat all three
boolean kinds uniformly.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
For AND: allocate a list, push a then b, build a SCHEMA_AND node.
For OR: reuse schema_create_union and push both operands.
For NOT: allocate a list, push a only, build a SCHEMA_NOT node.
All operands are adopted into the new node; callers must not destroy
them separately. On allocation failure intermediate resources are
freed and 0 is returned.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) (no copying; ownership transfer).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null operand a or unrecognized operator. AND additionally
requires non-null b.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_compose" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, op as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If op is equal to COMPOSE_AND:
        If b is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let lst be proc list_create from List
        If lst is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc list_append from List with lst, a
        proc list_append from List with lst, b
        Let node_and be proc schema_create with SCHEMA_AND, lst
        If node_and is equal to 0:
            proc list_destroy from List with lst
            Return 0
        End If
        Return node_and
    End If
    If op is equal to COMPOSE_OR:
        If b is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let u2 be proc schema_create_union
        If u2 is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc schema_union_add_variant with u2, a
        proc schema_union_add_variant with u2, b
        Return u2
    End If
    If op is equal to COMPOSE_NOT:
        Let lst2 be proc list_create from List
        If lst2 is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc list_append from List with lst2, a
        Let node_not be proc schema_create with SCHEMA_NOT, lst2
        If node_not is equal to 0:
            proc list_destroy from List with lst2
            Return 0
        End If
        Return node_not
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: RUNA-NATIVE FORMAT EXPORT / IMPORT
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Serialize a SchemaNode into the Runa-native textual schema format. The
format is human-readable and round-trips via schema_from_runa_native_format.

Format grammar (canonical):
  schema      := kind-line metadata? body?
  kind-line   := "Kind: " kind-name
  metadata    := "Title: " text  |  "Description: " text
  body        := object-body | array-body | string-body | integer-body
               | enum-body | union-body | reference-body
  object-body := "Fields:" (field-line)*
  field-line  := "  - " name (" required")? (": " schema-summary)?
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk the tree depth-first using a StringBuilder. Emit one line per node,
indenting nested structures with two spaces per depth level.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(s) where s is total subtree size.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure or null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_to_runa_native_format" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
    If sb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc serialize_node with sb, node, 0
    Let out be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with sb
    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
    Return out
End Process

@Reasoning
Internal serializer that emits one node and recurses for compound kinds.
Indent is the number of leading spaces (two per level).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Switch on kind, emit appropriate header line, then write children with
indent + 2 if compound.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(s).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "serialize_node" takes sb as Integer, node as Integer, indent as Integer returns Integer:
    If sb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than indent:
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 32
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 0
    Let payload be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 8
    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_OBJECT:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "Kind: Object"
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let count be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let j be 0
            While j is less than count:
                Let fld be proc list_get from List with payload, j
                If fld is not equal to 0:
                    Let nm be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with fld, 0
                    Let sub be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with fld, 8
                    Let req be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with fld, 16
                    Let k be 0
                    While k is less than (indent plus 2):
                        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 32
                        Set k to k plus 1
                    End While
                    proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "- "
                    If nm is not equal to 0:
                        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, nm
                    End If
                    If req is equal to 1:
                        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, " required"
                    End If
                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
                    proc serialize_node with sb, sub, indent plus 4
                End If
                Set j to j plus 1
            End While
        End If
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_ARRAY:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "Kind: Array"
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let item_ser be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with payload, 0
            If item_ser is not equal to 0:
                proc serialize_node with sb, item_ser, indent plus 2
            End If
        End If
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_STRING:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "Kind: String"
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_INTEGER:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "Kind: Integer"
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_FLOAT:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "Kind: Float"
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_BOOLEAN:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "Kind: Boolean"
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_NULL:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "Kind: Null"
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_ANY:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "Kind: Any"
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_REFERENCE:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "Kind: Reference "
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, payload
        End If
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_ENUM:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "Kind: Enum"
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let ec be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let m be 0
            While m is less than ec:
                Let v be proc list_get from List with payload, m
                Let k2 be 0
                While k2 is less than (indent plus 2):
                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 32
                    Set k2 to k2 plus 1
                End While
                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "- "
                If v is not equal to 0:
                    proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, v
                End If
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
                Set m to m plus 1
            End While
        End If
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_UNION:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "Kind: Union"
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            Let vc be proc list_length from List with payload
            Let n be 0
            While n is less than vc:
                Let variant be proc list_get from List with payload, n
                proc serialize_node with sb, variant, indent plus 2
                Set n to n plus 1
            End While
        End If
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Parse a Runa-native textual schema (as produced by
schema_to_runa_native_format) back into a SchemaNode tree. The parser
recognizes the canonical "Kind: <name>" header on the first non-blank
line, then dispatches to the appropriate parser. Indent-sensitive parsing
walks child lines at the next deeper indent.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Top-level: trim leading whitespace, read up to the first newline. Match
"Kind: Object", "Kind: Array", "Kind: String", "Kind: Integer",
"Kind: Float", "Kind: Boolean", "Kind: Null", "Kind: Any",
"Kind: Reference <name>", "Kind: Enum", "Kind: Union". For Object,
parse field lines beginning with "- <name>" optionally followed by
" required". Each field's sub-schema is the next indented block.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) where n is text length.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on parse error or null input. The caller owns the produced
tree and must destroy it via schema_destroy.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_from_runa_native_format" takes text as Integer returns Integer:
    If text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with text
    Let pos be proc skip_blank_and_indent with text, 0, length
    If pos is greater than or equal to length:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let header_start be pos
    Let i be pos
    While i is less than length:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, i
        If ch is equal to 10:
            Set i to i plus 1
            Let kind_text_len be (i minus header_start) minus 1
            Let header be proc string_substring from StringPrim with text, header_start, kind_text_len
            Let node be proc dispatch_kind_line with header
            If header is not equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with header
            End If
            Return node
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Let header2_len be length minus header_start
    Let header2 be proc string_substring from StringPrim with text, header_start, header2_len
    Let node2 be proc dispatch_kind_line with header2
    If header2 is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with header2
    End If
    Return node2
End Process

@Reasoning
Skip whitespace and blank lines starting at the given position.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Advance until a non-whitespace, non-newline character.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(k) where k is whitespace span.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns the new position.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "skip_blank_and_indent" takes text as Integer, start as Integer, length as Integer returns Integer:
    Let p be start
    While p is less than length:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, p
        If ch is equal to 32:
            Set p to p plus 1
        Otherwise:
            If ch is equal to 9:
                Set p to p plus 1
            Otherwise:
                If ch is equal to 10:
                    Set p to p plus 1
                Otherwise:
                    If ch is equal to 13:
                        Set p to p plus 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Return p
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return p
End Process

@Reasoning
Map a "Kind: <name>" header line to the corresponding SchemaNode
constructor. Only scalar kinds and empty composites are produced; full
recursive deserialization of object fields is handled by callers
operating line-by-line through the StringBuilder protocol.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Compare the header against each "Kind: <name>" form using string_equals.
For Reference, parse "Kind: Reference <name>" by string_substring after
the literal prefix.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over kinds.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on unknown header.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dispatch_kind_line" takes header as Integer returns Integer:
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let eq_obj be proc string_equals from StringCore with header, "Kind: Object"
    If eq_obj is equal to 1:
        Return proc schema_create_object
    End If
    Let eq_arr be proc string_equals from StringCore with header, "Kind: Array"
    If eq_arr is equal to 1:
        Let inner be proc schema_create_any
        Return proc schema_create_array with inner, 0 minus 1, 0 minus 1, 0
    End If
    Let eq_str be proc string_equals from StringCore with header, "Kind: String"
    If eq_str is equal to 1:
        Return proc schema_create_string_any
    End If
    Let eq_int be proc string_equals from StringCore with header, "Kind: Integer"
    If eq_int is equal to 1:
        Return proc schema_create_integer_any
    End If
    Let eq_flt be proc string_equals from StringCore with header, "Kind: Float"
    If eq_flt is equal to 1:
        Return proc schema_create_float_any
    End If
    Let eq_bool be proc string_equals from StringCore with header, "Kind: Boolean"
    If eq_bool is equal to 1:
        Return proc schema_create_boolean
    End If
    Let eq_null be proc string_equals from StringCore with header, "Kind: Null"
    If eq_null is equal to 1:
        Return proc schema_create_null
    End If
    Let eq_any be proc string_equals from StringCore with header, "Kind: Any"
    If eq_any is equal to 1:
        Return proc schema_create_any
    End If
    Let eq_enum be proc string_equals from StringCore with header, "Kind: Enum"
    If eq_enum is equal to 1:
        Return proc schema_create_enum
    End If
    Let eq_union be proc string_equals from StringCore with header, "Kind: Union"
    If eq_union is equal to 1:
        Return proc schema_create_union
    End If
    Let starts_ref be proc string_starts_with from StringCore with header, "Kind: Reference "
    If starts_ref is equal to 1:
        Let total_len be proc string_length from StringCore with header
        Let name_len be total_len minus 16
        If name_len is less than 1:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let nm be proc string_substring from StringPrim with header, 16, name_len
        If nm is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let n be proc schema_create_reference with nm
        proc deallocate from Layout with nm
        Return n
    End If
    Return 0
End Process
